### Goal:See a GitHub workflow in action

#To sign up for GitHub: 
Go to to "github.com" 
Select "Sign up"
Follow the prompts and fill in the required information to create an account.

#To create a new repository
Login into your github account
Click on the "+ dropdown button" in the top right corner
Select "New repository"
Give it a name and description 
Select if you want it to be public or private.

#To confirm Git installation locally 
Open the terminal, type "git --version"

#For a random SQL file
Using a text editor, write/paste a simple SQL query
Save it with the .sql extension

Add remote repo to GitHub: Open the terminal and navigate to the directory where the SQL file is saved. Then, run the following command: "git init". After that, run "git remote add origin https://github.com/[username]/[repository name].git", replacing the [username] and [repository name] with your own.

Add, commit, and push the file to the GitHub repo: Use the following commands to add, commit, and push the file to the repository: